<subSubSection id="7EFB11CC40778BFFF89D3ACB79079AFF" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="1E3E01B2F708A5BF173FDF8B8BBF7DBC" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Biology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79F3BFE576B077AAF8CEEEF6B9ACDF4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="BBB53AE737A72B4F33FB625855AC68A0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="0F113E8CBCBF1F4AA9E16965AEAF0516" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Habitats of Chinese Coelostoma A stone walls with running waters in forest (Yunnan) B wet stone walls with moss (Guangdong) C mountain stream in forest (Guangdong) D mountain river with rocky edges (Shanxi) E wastewater in city downtown (Guangdong) F lowland marshes with vegetation (Guangdong) G artificial lake (Yunnan) H brackish lagoon in mangrove reserve (Macao)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666197" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">15D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CCF4C8B879631A150CAF39E4B1CFC961" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Habitats of Chinese Coelostoma spp. A C. turnai Hebauer, 2006 active at wet rocky ground beside a river at night (Fujian) B C. sulcatum Pu, 1963 on sandy gutterway with shallow flowing waters at night (Guangdong) C C. phallicum Orchymont, 1940 hided under a brick beside the wastewater during the day (Guangdong) D C. phallicum Orchymont, 1940 dived under water and fed on algal mats at night (Guangdong) E C. bifidum Jia, Aston &amp; Fikacek on wet stone wall at night (Guangdong) F C. sulcatum Pu, 1963 on muddy edge of artificial lake at night (Yunnan) G C. nankunshanense sp. nov. on a stone in the middle of a forest stream at night (Guangdong) H C. surkhetensis Hebauer, 2002 in a wet stone on the edges of a forest stream at night (Xizang) I C. wui Orchymont, 1940 on the edges of a mountain river at night (Shanxi) J C. sulcatum Pu, 1963 on muddy edges of brackish lagoon at night, with a marine Amphipoda beside it (Macao) K C. nankunshanense sp. nov. mating at night (Guangdong) L C. wui Orchymont, 1940 ovipositing eggs on wet land at night (Shanxi)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666198" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">16I, L</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Collected on the ground beside a mountain river in Shanxi, active at night.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="71031433645CB2B4D154D67C99C24089" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EC1EBF68D7F0E01AC2AB671C744EE5AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3FB488521256059108C6C4DBDCCF0A49" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
The specimens we studied contained two different forms of male genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6DAB51EC637D9F975B558A4A6911CA3F" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Aedeagus of Coelostoma wui Orchymont, 1940 (dorsal view) A illustration by Orchymont (1940) B from Pingyi County (Shandong) C from Getiaopa (葛条爬) Village (Henan) D from Hanzhong (Shaanxi) E from Taoyuan County (Hunan) F from Quanzhou City (Zhejiang) G from Wuyishan (Fujian) H from Mt. Jiulianshan (Jiangxi) I from Mt. Chebaling (Guangdong). Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666196" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">14B-I</figureCitation>
). It may be inferred that the specimens treated by previous authors as 
<taxonomicName id="A3149835F8A274F3BCA8C0C6DFB61B54" class="Malacostraca" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. wui" order="Amphipoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wui">
<emphasis id="B0F28ADAD7B2E9F4425D508FEBF6F7D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. wui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Orchymont, 1940 possibly contain two species (see Discussion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2C744F914AAF2AE183F9C313D828C741" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A89BE5B5F597230121326E68C0D239DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="93436E4AB1F80E320B60D6F2228554A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
China (Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Shaanxi, Shandong, Shanxi, Taiwan, Xinjiang, Zhejiang), Korea. (
<bibRefCitation id="F93330B6DBA493B15BFACC95F78AE8D0" author="Hansen, M" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B8" refString="Hansen, M, 1999. World Catalogue of Insects 2: Hydrophiloidea (s. str.) (Coleoptera). Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="World Catalogue of Insects 2: Hydrophiloidea (s. str.) (Coleoptera)." year="1999">Hansen 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A7D9A911C87151544F0D6D1C5199C5E3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" author="Jia, F-L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="354 - 376" refId="B13" refString="Jia, F-L, Aston, P, Fikacek, M, 2014. Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae). Zootaxa 3887 (3): 354 - 376, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" title="Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" volume="3887" year="2014">Jia et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
